properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 14 at 10:14AM CST until February 14 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 40 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Blue Earth and Faribault Counties.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...These strong winds will also resulting in
blowing snow, which will lead to patchy icy conditions on area
roads where snow blows over the roadway.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
